And then, none of the one that has lived the history will ever forget the media circus that the president Bill Clinton has started lying during his second mandate on his sexual involvement with Monica Lewinsky.
The stories of cheating to the tests of the school and of the university are a legion.
There have been cases where the teachers have given the students the replies of the tests in order to be made well see on their evaluations of performance.
The mentors that should teach the opposite send the message according to which lie and the cheating are satisfactory.
How much deceit do we meet?
Towards a given day, the studies show that you can hear of 10 to 200 lies.
Actually, many of these are pious lies.
Another study has shown that the foreigners lie themselves to three resumptions in the 10 first minutes of their meeting.
To detect or to spot lies is an essential ability that each must acquire, at the same time for personal and professional reasons.
Far from being a similar boardgame to, let's say, of the riddles, where the objective is of exclaiming: "I have had you", the detection of the deceit is a serious branch of knowledge based on scientific data gathered in the course of the six last decades in prestigious universities having led a research in depth such projects, notably in psychology and in physiology.
One of the search results is that the oldest myths on the lie have been demystified.
The liars look at you in the eyes.
They do not stammer, blush or do always not fidget.
Not to conclude only the liars is difficult to detect and difficult to unmask.
A detector of qualified lie can discover the truth examining the structure of the declaration, the facial micro-expressions, the training of the question and the time of reply.
I have passed several years to examine scientific results in the vast body and always emergent from the knowledge on the deceit, and it is clear that the detection of the deceit is a modern ability that is easy-to-learn and useful to sail in our complex world - especially if your professional responsibilities include notably the hiring, the meetings, the negotiation or the management.
The good liars are skillful at well reading the others, taking them comfortably, managing their own emotions and intuitively detecting how the others perceive them.
We know of after investigations that the extroverts lie more that the introverts, what the men to call more lies "centered on them" even though the women say more lies "centered on the others" - usually to protect the feelings from somebody that the married people lie less often to their partners than the people not married (but that the lies that they tell have tendency to be enormous).
We also know that if you are perceived as a heathen, the others are going to feel less culprit of lying to you.
How can you say if anybody lies?
First and Foremost, observe the normal behavior of your subject.
It is what one calls "to establish the mark data".
That helps to supply a reference point to measure the ulterior changes.
Observe the posture of your subject, the laugh, the vocal quality.
You must know if somebody moves in a normal way his feet permanently in order to not launch unfair accusations when you see it move the feet in the middle of the meeting.
Then search for clues of verbal and not verbal deceitful behaviors.
Consider these clues as red flags, not of the proofs of the deceit.
The deceitful people can immobilize the top of the body while they try to remember their history, they can point their feet at the door, bend themselves to an exit, change posture in a significant way or present a relief of "post-interview" - one exaggerated sigh of relief, one change of posture when all the difficult questions are past.
The interrogators indicate often that the maintenance is just finished to try to start the post-interview reaction fakely.
Also, mind the vocabulary of your subject.
The famous Scott Peterson has veered using the past all claiming that his murdered woman was alive, starting a national research to find it.
The deceitful individuals can also use an outdistanced language: "I have not had sexual relationships with this woman... Miss Lewinsky" or to repeat entirely a difficult question.
The most common verbal indicators are subtle.
Somebody can use much of "language of wood" during his reply to a difficult question: "Eh well... for true statement... if I remember goods... to my knowledge."
That makes the reply perceptive rather than factual and is often a red flag.
There is not magic formula for the detection of lies, but the development of the abilities to recognize the deceit is possible.
These abilities will improve the chances of whom of avoiding the victimisation by swindlers in their professional and personal life.
